Today, Chief Kensington Adebutu, fondly addressed as Baba Ijebu, was joined by eminent individuals across Nigeria as he was installed as the Odole Odua by the Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi. Former President, Olusegun Obasanjo; Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo; Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State; Governor Babjide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State and Governor Isiaka Oyetola were in attendance. Others are Senator Oluremi Tinubu; Former Governor of Ogun State, Chief Olusegun Osoba and his successor, Otunba Gbenga Daniel; Minister of Interior, Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola; the Akarigbo of Remoland, Oba Babatunde Ajayi and many more. While blessing the new Odole Odua, Oba Ogunwusi said the highly revered title was in recognition of Adebutu’s enormous contributions to the development of Yoruba land and Nigeria as a whole; charging him that his installation was a call to do more. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.